<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1437,1493,2023]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral to bathyal species, known from infralittoral to 
<quantity box="[1166,1240,1925,1951]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="m" value="440.0">440 m</quantity>
on soft bottoms, mostly mud, muddy sand and possibly also sand (Miller 1986; 
<bibRefCitation author="Berenger, L. &amp; Pariset, M. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[867,1102,1961,1988]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" refId="ref51601" refString="Berenger, L., Pariset, M. &amp; Louisy, P. (2015) Signalisation de / Record of Lesueurigobius suerii, 17 June 2015 (obs. 22 May 2015, photo  498). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2015">
Bérenger 
<emphasis box="[978,1028,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rufray, X. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[1115,1326,1961,1987]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" refId="ref63986" refString="Rufray, X., Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P. (2016) Signalisation de / Record of Lesueurigobius suerii, 25 August 2016 (obs. 14 August 2016, photo  2781). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.) Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2016">
Rufray 
<emphasis box="[1201,1251,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goren, M. &amp; Danovaro, R. &amp; Rothman, S. B. S. &amp; Mienis, H. K. &amp; Galil, B. S." pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref55731" refString="Goren, M., Danovaro, R., Rothman, S. B. S., Mienis, H. K. &amp; Galil, B. S. (2019) Snapshot of the upper slope macro- and megafauna of the Southeastern Mediterranean Sea: Ecological diversity and protection. Vie et Milieu, 69, 233 - 248." type="journal article" year="2019">
Goren 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
